      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="does-webflow-need-plugins-for-seo-like-wordpress"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No, Webflow does not use plugins. Most SEO features are built into the platform. You do not need Yoast or Rank Math equivalents. The trade-off is less automation. WordPress plugins can auto-generate meta descriptions and schema. In Webflow, you configure these manually or use third-party tools like Semflow.</p></div></div>
